{
  "answer": "**The ghazal is Allama Iqbal's *Zamana dekhe ga jab mere dil se mahshar uthe ga guftugu ka*, chapter 6 of *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*.**[^1]\n\nThis poem features the requested wave-pearl couplet:\n\n> The river's wave began to say, \"My glory comes from journeying,\"  \n> The pearl replied, \"To stay inside is the source of my honor's sheen.\"[^2]\n\nAnd later, the rose-blood couplet:\n\n> Such Perfect Oneness is revealed, if with a needle you but prod,  \n> From the rose's vein, I know for sure, would fall a drop of human blood.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, ch. 6 ([/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/06-zamana-dekhe-ga-jab-mere-dil-se-mahshar-uthe-ga-gu/translation/](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/06-zamana-dekhe-ga-jab-mere-dil-se-mahshar-uthe-ga-gu/translation/)).\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, ch. 6, [p-26a389](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/06-zamana-dekhe-ga-jab-mere-dil-se-mahshar-uthe-ga-gu/translation/#p-26a389).\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, ch. 6, [p-30ffa7](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/06-zamana-dekhe-ga-jab-mere-dil-se-mahshar-uthe-ga-gu/translation/#p-30ffa7).",
